caption: Pinched is one of my favorite restaurants ever. I started going to the original Lombard location when I lived there and would go there at least twice a month. Now that I am in the city, I was thrilled when Pinched on the River was introduced.  The food is phenomenal. Original recipes, quality ingredients, and amazing flavor. Haven't anything like this anywhere. SO GOOD.

Please follow, like, and actually GO to ➡️  Pinched on the River in Downtown Chicago @ one of the nicest neighborhoods. The Food was absolutely to die for; But not just that, we went unexpected; with a party of over 10 The staff went above and beyond to accommodate us immediately. I was absolutely blown away on how the staff was on the ball every minute of every hour during our stay. Very well done. I would definitely recommend and will be back soon!
Great restaurant, the food is amazing and we really had a good time there. The owner is also really nice! I highly recommend.
Fresh tasty food! The restaurant is very clean and the service was amazing. I look forward to my next visit!
Yeah no lies told.   This place is fire go there great food

My wife, daughter, and I dropped by for lunch after an appointment at Rush where my daughter had surgery the day before. The owner, and staff we’re extremely helpful and let my daughter take the elevator normally used by tenants. The food was amazing, the staff was very nice and friendly! And top all that off with warm beignet(or twelve)! Place was fabulous!!!!!! We will definitely be back!’n
Great place to eat. Wonderful ambience and pleasant staff.

"Mediterranean restaurant with mostly Indian food" food does not taste good, pita bread is like eating sand, probably frozen and reheated. Service and ambient is good, but that's it. Also you don't get glasses for soda, they let you drink it out of can, and the plates are plastic. It's like a bad fast-food with really nice ambient. Wouldn't recommend.
Great little spot! Their lunch to-go boxes are the perfect mid-week lunch option. The food is always great and they have a nice patio along the water in the summer.
This place was a revelation for me. Best traditional Serbian barbecue in Chicago. Will he back for sure. Highly recomended

This place is Awesome, very nice atmosphere and the food was incredibly authentic. Its authenticity  took me for a little journey back home. This is like Soul Food for me. Me and my wife will be back for sure with friends and family.

Great place! I had the pita roll with beef shivac and it was tasty! They have good beers(try the IPA) and service is excellent. Don't be confused by the small front entrance, there is a huge area downstairs and a patio!
Amazing food !!!!   Wonderful service!  So much Flavor and honestly the best falafel we’ve ever eaten❤️
Delicious, friendly, fresh!! We loved it!!
Good food, great drinks, nice view and excellent service!
A great riverside eatery.. loved the food and the view.
Delicious food & wine choices accompanied with beautiful outside seating along the Ogden Slip (waterway).
There's no place to stand at the slip anymore. They just took all the space.
Great outdoor seating on the water, great friendly service and food selection
Good food, great ambience
Laid back setting with an awesome view and delicious food! A delight to the sight and the palette.
AMAZING atmosphere, even more AMAZING food. So flavorful and delicious. Staff was perfect too! This am absolutely hidden GEM in the best location!
Falafel salad was excellent
Delicious food, nice wine selection and fantastic service. The outdoor patio on the river is awesome, plenty of space for social distancing and nice views of the city and ogden slip.
The food was absolutely spectacular. Everything that came out was absolutely delicious and the wine pairing was perfect. Definitely one of my favorite places
Good food and ambiance  Be wary of tipping twice if a party of 6 ( and they use an app so you can’t tell like when it’s usually a bill)
Food, service, wine. Everything was very impressive. Always amazing!!!!
Nice riverside patio and delicious good. Very nice service
Great food and an awesome staff specially Maria! I can’t wait to to come back!
Great food, fabulous view!
Lot of fresh air 😂😂😂
I love the scenery, low key and beautiful! Not a fan of the beef but everything else was fresh and delicious. Great customer service also.
Very nice service, tables outside by the canal. Quiet. Food is fresh and tasty.
This food is excellent. The best Mediterranean food in the area and very well priced. Definitely will return again to enjoy the outdoor seating along the river
Delicious food, good location, wonderful view! 💯🥇
Delicious food, very friendly service, great location !
Chicken shawarma was delicious

Service is always great. Food is even better. This is one of my favorite places to eat out on any given night. They have a great bar in the restaurant and for any beer drinkers, they have an amazing IPA that’s made just for this restaurant. Would highly recommend!
Great place, delicious food, convenient location, friendly staff.
Delicious and fresh

Falafel salad with garlic sauce was delicious. The food is decently priced and the environment was really pleasant. I'm sure it would be even better on a nice day when the patio isn't covered in snow. I can't say enough about the staff. 3 different people ensured I was taken care of in a helpful and not helicopter type way. Highly recommend.
Outstanding mediterranean food, great music, lovely atmosphere!
Excellent food and location. We stopped there with the kiddos and the staff was great at accommodating us. The food is truly delicious. We’ll be back!
Best place I’ve been too so far, amazing food with delicious flavors. The hospitality from all was amazing and quick. The beignets I highly recommend ordering for dessert!

Amazing fresh food 👌🏼 Perfect meal to grab very light and filling. Great service and huge selection in wines. I suggest the Rice Bowl with Beef Chevapi or with Chicken Shwarma and they also have great sides to choose from with your meal. Would definitely come again and bring the family and friends to try this place out. PS: (Also great for the summer with outdoor seating by the river)
Amazing, tasty food! I love the flavors that you can choose from for each dish.
Great menu ,great management...
Just had a late lunch and enjoyed every single bite of Pita Roll, I highly recommend this place. I’ll be coming back when I’m in Chicago

The place is really cute and modern. I got a pita with beef chevap, olives, tabouli, red and regular hummus, and garlic sauce. IT WAS DELICIOUS!!! Especially the beef tasted excellent! Highly recommend trying this place out.
Tried it for the first time, and food was GREAT!! Defiantly will go back!! Staff great as well.

Hello everyone! Anyone visiting or in the area, I recommend that you visit this restaurant. The hosts and the owner are very welcoming. The food and dessert are the best experience. The atmosphere is great. Great music, great vibe, perfect set-up of the whole restaurant. Also, it includes a bar. In brief, the food is always made fresh and it's healthy! I'll leave the rest to you! Go enjoy and take your partners, friends and relatives and have fun!!!!

Great spot offering some comfort Mediterranean food! Come here for a quick, casual and yummy lunch in Streeterville. You can basically build up your own salad, sandwich or rice bowl by adding one protein and up to 4 toppings. The spicy beef with lite garlic sauce was amazing! Shout outs to the soft and warm pita.

Absolutely loved this place! The restaurant is spotless. The food is so fresh and so, so good. The staff was amazing; they were super helpful and incredibly welcoming. They walked me through the menu and even told me where to go for the best views in the city. This was truly a great experience.
Love the view to the river :)
Hidden srcret fresh and good
Didn't expect it to be so delicious! The pita was so soft. Could not stop eating.

Overall pretty tasty! Had the chicken kebab. One of the pieces of chicken was pretty rubbery but the others were great. Serving size could have been bigger in terms of the chicken. The garlic sauce and tabouli in particular were flavorful.

Mediocre at best. Highlight was the gluten free pita. Same can't be said for the regular pita (nothing closet to Naf Nafs). Both meals (rice bowl chicken shawarma and salad chicken kabob) were ultimately lacking flavor. Sauce was provided in a small spoon, with extra 'spoons' of sauce at $1 each. Money better spent elsewhere.
Delicious!

Overall a very good Mediterranean place.  It is not table service per se. You order at the counter and they bring your food to wherever you choose to sit. My guy was super frazzled (new maybe? ) but everyone else was calm,  friendly,  and fast.  Ordered the rice bowl. You pick one bowl type, one protein and 4 toppings  plus a "dab of sauce". Everything is accurate to what they describe.  Mine was a scoop of rice (very good), good portion of shawarma (not overdone like some places.  Good flavor overall). I got hummus, olives,  feta,  and Mediterranean salad.  Super fresh. I think I may have gotten the wrong hummus,  but if not, that was my only dislike.  It was not smooth and didn't taste like chickpeas. Can't say it was bad just not what I was expecting.  Could gave used seasoning for sure.  The dab of sauce is too small! I got 2 and still too small!  I love sauce and the garlic one was great. They could be a bit nicer on the sauce portion. But the best.  The absolute BEST homemade pita EVER.  Lastly,  tried the begniets. Fine. Look like pillows like they should.  Too dense.   Get the baklava instead.
Great food. Excellent staff. The place looks clean and cozy

We walked into Pinched an hour before the restaurant opened and the owner personally walked us through their space and menu. The restaurant is in a quiet, secluded location right by the river. The food was fresh and terrific (the falafels were different than anything I’ve ever had and I really liked them) and everyone that we interacted with was very friendly.

This place is amazing...the food was great, fresh and delicious.  Excellent service.  The staff was very welcoming and polite.  They knew the menu inside and out and were very well prepared.  The place was spotless.  Very very clean.  Surprisingly, the prices were very reasonable considering the location.  Definitely recommend it as I am going back to eat again there soon.
Good food, awesome presentation and good service. Nice location.
Ranka is the owner and such a nice woman. The food is delicious, the service is wicked fast, and the location is perfect.

Fresh, home made food, beautifully presented. Very flavorful.  Our entire family each got different things and everyone enjoyed their food. We met the owner and the service was wonderful.  Also great prices for a generous serving. Lots of seating downstairs inside or outside by the river.

If you want fresh, delicious, and cheap food. Come here. The cuisine is perfect and you will not regret it. My lady and I got 2 huge plates of food with a beer for $40 and the owner brought us out a dessert on the house. Which was also delicious.  Highly recommend if you are in the city of Chicago.

Pleasantly surprised by this place. Great food and a nice place to sit. Wondered how it would compare with the chains like Naf Naf and definitely think its better. Not to mention more space and drinks. Only mild critique would be the fact that you can only get one sauce without paying $1.50. I always prefer combining a spicy sauce with tzatziki or garlic.
Amazing food and service!
Wonderful evening at Pinched On The River! Fantastic staff and delicious food, can’t wait to come back! 🍻

(Translated by Google) A small haven of peace, perfect terrace, not for the service, but for a salad and a glass of wine!  (Original) Un petit havre de paix, terrasse parfaite, pas pour le service, mais pour une salade et un verre de vin !

I love this place, we live locally and go at least once per week. I always get the salad bowls but with different combinations of protein & toppings. The gazpacho is fantastic and the SOP beer made special for them is awesome. And you have to save room for the beignets!  So happy I can get fresh, heart healthy, high quality food in the neighborhood.

ABSOLUTELY PHENOMENAL!!! The service was spectacular! Everything was so fresh and delicious. This place is brand new and really is a hidden gem 💎💎💎  I didn't even know that North Pier was a "Thing"! Waterfront dining in a quiet little corner corner of the city that you need to see 👀  The owners Ranka and Nasi are wonderful hosts and so accessible. They came out to take this picture with me when I asked for a photo. They are the nicest people and I am happy to support their business!  The are the only business on the water with a liquor license 🍷🍷  Their wine selection is fantastic and splitting a bottle (or two) with my friend was a great way to spend the afternoon.  All and all I know you will not be disappointed.  If coming in from the street just walk straight down the hallway and down the stairs. They are next to the bowling alley. You won't regret it!

Stopped in to just kill some time before the fireworks. The owner came out and personally greeted us and spent several minutes chatting about a number of different things. What a great atmosphere, great service, and just overall really good vibe.
They have amazing gluten-free options! Ordered the ordered the gluten-free pita roll with chicken kebab, red and green slaw Mediterranean salad. The wine selection was fantastic as well!

Finally authentic Mediterranean food in Streeterville!!  I ordered the Salad bowl with chicken and it was tasty, fresh and filling but yet light enough that I could go back to work after the meal. The restaurant itself is very cool and the patio on Ogden Slip "the river" is AWESOME! Such a peaceful spot to relax and have a nice conversation over a drink and a healthy meal (I highly recommend the Froze' if you're in the mood for a cold drink).  To top it all off, Pinched is the only place in Chicago that serves beignets and they are GREAT!
Great food, awesome presentation and good service.  Be careful with the spicy as its borderline thai spicy.  Which is great if your into that sort of thing.
Amazing food, location and staff.
Great food and a great atmosphere. I love the fast casual, where you order at a countertop and then sit along the River. The food is delicious! Highly suggest it.
Best restaurant  in Chicago área. The food was perfect, and service was 5 star.
Great place for Mediterranean food👍

Great food! Started with falafel and they were good.  Got the spicy chevap bowl with poblano hummus, onions, cabbage, bean and corn, garlic sauce and schug - the bowl was good size and the pita was great but sauces were small.  Ate the food before I took a picture.  Have a rewards program for frequent dining and will come back.
Great little quiet spot - food is fantastic, nice wine and beer selection, amazing location.

What a fabulous place, I am so happy to welcome Mediterranean food to streeterville!! With a patio that overlooks the Ogden slip, it's going to be a summer go-to for sure.  Everything was fresh and hot and well seasoned without being overpowering or too salty.  Plus there's fresh beignets! What more could you ask for.
